The Speaker of House of Representatives, Femi Gbajabiamila says a second batch of amendments to the 1999 constitution will soon start. Gbajabiamila disclosed this while fielding questions from reporters at the Government House, Ilorin. He said there will be more devolution of power from the exclusive to the concurrent list in the new amendment. The Speaker also disclosed that both chambers of the national assembly will harmonize the amendments and also send to the state houses of assembly. The Kwara State governor stressed the need to have more women in government especially thirty-five per cent affirmative. Political appointments he added should be increased for womenfolk and urged other states to emulate Kwara State in this regard.